00:00:51.580 --> 00:00:54.500
Let's dive into this deepfake explainer.

00:00:54.500 --> 00:00:56.883
So what exactly is a deepfake?

00:00:57.780 --> 00:01:00.560
Simply put, deepfakes are videos

00:01:00.560 --> 00:01:02.570
in which one person's face

00:01:02.570 --> 00:01:05.810
has been replaced by a
computer-generated face

00:01:05.810 --> 00:01:08.640
that closely looks like another person.

00:01:08.640 --> 00:01:10.160
The term was born in Reddit

00:01:10.160 --> 00:01:12.110
when members of a group called Deepfake

00:01:13.100 --> 00:01:16.800
used AI to put celebrities
faces on porn actors.

00:01:16.800 --> 00:01:18.763
Take a look at this Tom Cruise video.

00:01:20.740 --> 00:01:21.740
- What's up, TikTok?

00:01:24.490 --> 00:01:26.290
You guys cool if I play some sports?

00:01:27.620 --> 00:01:30.250
- Looks close to reality

00:01:30.250 --> 00:01:32.760
yet it is a deepfake.

00:01:32.760 --> 00:01:35.010
The programs that create deepfakes

00:01:35.010 --> 00:01:39.340
usually use two different
AIs at the same time.

00:01:39.340 --> 00:01:42.460
The first one will scan images, videos,

00:01:42.460 --> 00:01:44.160
and audio of the victim

00:01:44.160 --> 00:01:46.993
and then generate a
tampered image or video.

00:01:48.040 --> 00:01:49.640
- I'm gonna show you some magic.

00:01:51.200 --> 00:01:55.170
- The second AI will
compare them to real images

00:01:55.170 --> 00:01:57.200
and report any difference.

00:01:57.200 --> 00:02:00.290
Finally, the first AI
will receive this feedback

00:02:00.290 --> 00:02:02.420
and repeat the process several times

00:02:02.420 --> 00:02:04.760
until the second one can't tell a fake

00:02:04.760 --> 00:02:06.560
from the real thing anymore.

00:02:06.560 --> 00:02:08.660
This technology has evolved

00:02:08.660 --> 00:02:12.160
to the point that it is
accessible to nearly everyone

00:02:12.160 --> 00:02:14.100
and it is likely to get easier

00:02:14.100 --> 00:02:16.530
as computing power improves,

00:02:16.530 --> 00:02:20.020
but the power of deepfakes
is even more sinister

00:02:20.020 --> 00:02:22.460
than might originally seen.

00:02:22.460 --> 00:02:23.930
Channel 4 in England

00:02:23.930 --> 00:02:25.700
made a statement with the video

00:02:25.700 --> 00:02:29.570
known as Queen Elizabeth's
"Alternative Christmas Speech"

00:02:29.570 --> 00:02:30.680
in 2020.

00:02:30.680 --> 00:02:31.640
The video began

00:02:31.640 --> 00:02:33.860
with the Queen addressing
the British people

00:02:33.860 --> 00:02:35.870
as she does every year

00:02:35.870 --> 00:02:38.130
but then things got twisted

00:02:38.130 --> 00:02:39.930
when she began to make jokes

00:02:39.930 --> 00:02:43.200
about public crown
scandals from that year.

00:02:43.200 --> 00:02:44.850
Only when she stood up to dance,

00:02:44.850 --> 00:02:48.141
people started to realize
it wasn't really her.

00:02:48.141 --> 00:02:49.746
♪ Don't need your love ♪

00:02:49.746 --> 00:02:51.751
♪ I'm a sinner ♪

00:02:51.751 --> 00:02:54.150
♪ There's my lover crying ♪

00:02:54.150 --> 00:02:55.890
The video raised awareness,

00:02:55.890 --> 00:02:57.850
as well as some eyebrows

00:02:57.850 --> 00:02:59.420
and opened up the conversation

00:02:59.420 --> 00:03:02.790
about the seriousness and
even maybe the dangers

00:03:02.790 --> 00:03:05.010
of deepfake technology.

00:03:05.010 --> 00:03:06.880
And that's just the beginning.

00:03:06.880 --> 00:03:08.720
Deepfakes can be used in warfare

00:03:08.720 --> 00:03:10.930
to raise or kill military morale.

00:03:10.930 --> 00:03:12.520
In March 2022,

00:03:12.520 --> 00:03:15.330
Meta removed a video posted on Facebook

00:03:15.330 --> 00:03:19.386
of President Zelensky
encouraging Ukrainian people-

00:03:19.386 --> 00:03:24.386
(President Zelensky speaking
in foreign language)

00:03:29.640 --> 00:03:31.040
To lay down their arms,

00:03:31.040 --> 00:03:34.160
after realizing it was a deepfake.

00:03:34.160 --> 00:03:36.500
The video went viral on the platform

00:03:36.500 --> 00:03:41.470
and was shown in TV 24's hacked
website as breaking news.

00:03:41.470 --> 00:03:44.730
The Ukrainian president
had to debunk the scam

00:03:44.730 --> 00:03:48.390
posting a video of himself
on his own Telegram channel

00:03:48.390 --> 00:03:50.540
supporting Ukrainian troops.

00:03:50.540 --> 00:03:53.560
Not everything is merely
misinformation though,

00:03:53.560 --> 00:03:57.790
deepfakes can be used to
target pretty much everyone,

00:03:57.790 --> 00:04:00.740
from celebrities and political figures,

00:04:00.740 --> 00:04:02.350
to regular citizens.

00:04:02.350 --> 00:04:04.590
It was only two years ago that Sensity,

00:04:04.590 --> 00:04:08.590
an intelligence company
specialized in visual threats,

00:04:08.590 --> 00:04:12.670
recorded 85,000 deepfake videos.

00:04:12.670 --> 00:04:15.450
These meant to destroy reputations.

00:04:15.450 --> 00:04:16.840
These videos consisted

00:04:16.840 --> 00:04:19.650
of creating non-consensual pornography

00:04:19.650 --> 00:04:22.860
or even inciting fear and violence

00:04:22.860 --> 00:04:27.340
through incendiary speeches
from targeted politicians.

00:04:27.340 --> 00:04:29.220
These incidents are getting worse

00:04:29.220 --> 00:04:31.210
and involve digital abuse,

00:04:31.210 --> 00:04:35.670
such as harassment,
blackmail, and public shaming.

00:04:35.670 --> 00:04:39.610
Of course, the ability of
putting someone's face or voice

00:04:39.610 --> 00:04:41.280
into another person

00:04:41.280 --> 00:04:43.550
presents a huge opportunity

00:04:43.550 --> 00:04:46.440
to a bunch of unscrupulous people.

00:04:46.440 --> 00:04:49.040
In 2019, "The Wall
Street Journal" reported

00:04:49.040 --> 00:04:52.250
that this CEO of a UK-based company

00:04:52.250 --> 00:04:54.970
believed he was on the phone with his boss

00:04:54.970 --> 00:04:59.970
when he instantly
transferred 220,000 euros

00:05:00.200 --> 00:05:01.970
following his orders

00:05:01.970 --> 00:05:02.850
only to find out

00:05:02.850 --> 00:05:05.350
he was actually speaking to scammers

00:05:05.350 --> 00:05:08.000
who imitated his employer's voice

00:05:08.000 --> 00:05:10.830
using AI technology.

00:05:10.830 --> 00:05:12.900
Many experts state that deepfakes

00:05:12.900 --> 00:05:16.020
are the biggest cybersecurity
threat nowadays,

00:05:16.020 --> 00:05:18.690
and they're kind of right.

00:05:18.690 --> 00:05:20.120
Recent tech developments

00:05:20.120 --> 00:05:23.470
have advanced towards
biometrical technologies,

00:05:23.470 --> 00:05:25.000
from cell phone locks,

00:05:25.000 --> 00:05:27.800
to bank accounts and passports.

00:05:27.800 --> 00:05:29.210
These types of security

00:05:29.210 --> 00:05:31.930
that rely heavily on face recognition

00:05:31.930 --> 00:05:35.210
seem to be at risk with deepfakes evolving

00:05:35.210 --> 00:05:38.230
at such a fast pace.

00:05:38.230 --> 00:05:41.110
Big tech companies are aware
of this harmful potential

00:05:41.110 --> 00:05:43.210
and are coming up with powerful tools,

00:05:43.210 --> 00:05:45.480
including cutting edge technology,

00:05:45.480 --> 00:05:48.200
to detect this kind of video.

00:05:48.200 --> 00:05:51.280
Wondering how to recognize
a deepfake video?

00:05:51.280 --> 00:05:52.540
Some experts say

00:05:52.540 --> 00:05:55.490
it's the blinking that gives fakes away.

00:05:55.490 --> 00:05:57.130
It's hard for an AI

00:05:57.130 --> 00:05:59.660
to closely recreate human behavior.

00:05:59.660 --> 00:06:00.493
As a result,

00:06:00.493 --> 00:06:04.160
deepfakes blink much less
frequently than humans.

00:06:04.160 --> 00:06:07.190
Maybe one of the most talked
about dangers of deepfake

00:06:07.190 --> 00:06:09.550
is related to politics.

00:06:09.550 --> 00:06:12.660
In the 2020 US presidential elections,

00:06:12.660 --> 00:06:14.300
many feared that deepfakes

00:06:14.300 --> 00:06:16.630
could influence the voting results.

00:06:16.630 --> 00:06:19.470
Fortunately, these fears
didn't materialize,

00:06:19.470 --> 00:06:22.150
with the only deepfakes
related to the elections

00:06:22.150 --> 00:06:23.500
being satirical.

00:06:23.500 --> 00:06:27.710
However, the US government
established a deepfake task force

00:06:27.710 --> 00:06:30.660
which aims to safeguard the
population from scammers

00:06:30.660 --> 00:06:32.620
who want to defraud America

00:06:32.620 --> 00:06:35.190
using artificial intelligence.

00:06:35.190 --> 00:06:36.550
There are already fears

00:06:36.550 --> 00:06:38.170
that if people don't get better

00:06:38.170 --> 00:06:41.580
at differentiating fakes
from authentic videos,

00:06:41.580 --> 00:06:44.180
it could cost them prison sentences,

00:06:44.180 --> 00:06:45.860
fake accusations,

00:06:45.860 --> 00:06:48.080
or even false fakes.

00:06:48.080 --> 00:06:50.070
Just to give you an example,

00:06:50.070 --> 00:06:51.810
three years ago in Malaysia,

00:06:51.810 --> 00:06:54.380
a politician was caught on several videos

00:06:54.380 --> 00:06:56.560
proving his sexual misconduct

00:06:56.560 --> 00:07:00.810
to which he sustained were manipulated

00:07:00.810 --> 00:07:02.750
when they actually weren't.

00:07:02.750 --> 00:07:03.583
Oh, and by the way,

00:07:03.583 --> 00:07:05.330
do you remember that case I mentioned

00:07:05.330 --> 00:07:07.150
at the beginning of this video,

00:07:07.150 --> 00:07:09.470
the one about the cheerleader's mom?

00:07:09.470 --> 00:07:12.590
Well, they couldn't prove
the video was manipulated

00:07:12.590 --> 00:07:15.910
and even many experts
concluded it might be real.

00:07:15.910 --> 00:07:19.000
The woman's most high
profile charges were dropped

00:07:19.000 --> 00:07:22.470
not without first making it
to international headlines

00:07:22.470 --> 00:07:26.190
and seriously damaging her reputation.

00:07:26.190 --> 00:07:28.330
Not everything is grim though,

00:07:28.330 --> 00:07:32.510
there have been positive
uses of deepfake technology.

00:07:32.510 --> 00:07:33.343
For example,

00:07:33.343 --> 00:07:36.160
it is being used in training
videos for companies,

00:07:36.160 --> 00:07:39.600
and there are TV shows
like "Sassy Justice"

00:07:39.600 --> 00:07:42.720
that create characters faces using AI.

00:07:42.720 --> 00:07:43.830
There're even cases

00:07:43.830 --> 00:07:46.680
like the "Welcome to Chechnya" documentary

00:07:46.680 --> 00:07:49.490
in which the creators
use deepfake technology

00:07:49.490 --> 00:07:53.460
to protect the identity
of the LGBTQ+ community

00:07:53.460 --> 00:07:56.540
they were portraying in Southern Russia.

00:07:56.540 --> 00:08:01.340
So, is it a good or a bad technology?

00:08:01.340 --> 00:08:03.930
Before jumping to my final conclusions,

00:08:03.930 --> 00:08:05.470
remember to like this video,

00:08:05.470 --> 00:08:06.610
if you haven't already,

00:08:06.610 --> 00:08:08.490
and to subscribe for more content

00:08:08.490 --> 00:08:11.470
on technology and cyber security.

00:08:11.470 --> 00:08:14.560
The technology behind
deepfakes is very new

00:08:14.560 --> 00:08:17.340
and maybe we shouldn't judge it just yet.

00:08:17.340 --> 00:08:18.670
Like any technology,

00:08:18.670 --> 00:08:20.670
it can bring positive innovations

00:08:20.670 --> 00:08:24.630
regardless of the fact that
there is a dark side to it.

00:08:24.630 --> 00:08:26.460
One thing I'm certainly worried about

00:08:26.460 --> 00:08:29.510
is something called the Liar's Dividend.

00:08:29.510 --> 00:08:31.120
According to the concept,

00:08:31.120 --> 00:08:34.640
deepfakes might allow
criminals to walk free.

00:08:34.640 --> 00:08:36.400
This is already happening

00:08:36.400 --> 00:08:40.020
and it's hindering legal
processes along the way.

00:08:40.020 --> 00:08:42.590
Experts suggest, in the coming years,

00:08:42.590 --> 00:08:46.080
we should expect more and
more of this to happen.

